            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Supports local economic activity through $2.78 million in recent NASA Science spending within NY-17.\n* Sustains high-tech jobs and R&D at local firms including Teledyne LeCroy, Teledyne Digital Imaging, and All Tech Electronics.\n* Directly benefits educational institutions and regional partners like The Trustees of Columbia University who support NASA science efforts.\n* Drives local innovation in specialized electronics and imaging technology critical to the broader U.S. aerospace and defense supply chain.",
